<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Vin's Blog (Archlinux)</title><link>http://carlosvin.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="http://carlosvin.github.io/en/categories/archlinux.xml" type="application/rss+xml" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 13 May 2014 16:38:11 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola &lt;http://getnikola.com/&gt;</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Remove orphaned packages (Linux)</title><link>http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/linux-remove-orphaned-files.html</link><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;When we install a package in most of Linux distributions, the package system installs other packages needed by the package that we actually want to install.
If we uninstall the package, its dependencies won't be uninstalled, these unused dependencies are called orphaned packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="contents topic" id="remove-orphaned-packages"&gt;
&lt;p class="topic-title first"&gt;Remove orphaned packages&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class="reference internal" href="http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/linux-remove-orphaned-files.html#archlinux" id="id3"&gt;Archlinux&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class="reference internal" href="http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/linux-remove-orphaned-files.html#debian" id="id4"&gt;Debian&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="archlinux"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://archlinux.org/"&gt;Archlinux&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash literal-block"&gt;
pacman -Rsn &lt;span class="k"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;pacman -Qdtq&lt;span class="k"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How does the command work?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman -Qdt&lt;/code&gt; list all orphaned packages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman -Rsn&lt;/code&gt; uninstall the listed packages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="debian"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://debian.org/"&gt;Debian&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash literal-block"&gt;
apt-get remove --purge &lt;span class="k"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;deborphan&lt;span class="k"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>Linux</category><category>Archlinux</category><category>Debian</category><category>Tips and Tricks</category><guid>http://carlosvin.github.io/en/posts/linux-remove-orphaned-files.html</guid><pubDate>Tue, 02 Oct 2012 11:30:02 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>